</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,151,860]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[199,566,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks and comparative notes.</emphasis>
This taxon differs from the other two species of the group, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1232,1435,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratychioides">
<emphasis box="[1232,1435,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. paratychioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Korotyaev" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[200,367,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desertorum">
<emphasis box="[200,367,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. desertorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the segment 2 of antennal funicle only moderately longer than wide. Moreover it differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[214,419,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratychioides">
<emphasis box="[214,419,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. paratychioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shorter rostrum and the elytra with longer scales, and from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Korotyaev" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[1189,1356,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="desertorum">
<emphasis box="[1189,1356,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">M. desertorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the cylindrical rostrum and the narrower and flat eyes.
</paragraph>
